This article is a message from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, stating the continuation of the national emergency with respect to the stabilization of Iraq. The President has published a notice in the Federal Register, stating that the national emergency declared in 2003 is to continue beyond May 22, 2012. The message explains that obstacles to the reconstruction of Iraq and the development of its institutions continue to pose a threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States. The President has determined that it is necessary to continue the national emergency and maintain the measures taken to deal with it. The administration will also evaluate Iraq's progress in resolving outstanding debts and claims from the previous regime. The President may decide to continue the prohibitions on certain judicial processes related to Iraqi assets and petroleum products. The message is signed by President Barack Obama.